    <bioghist encodinganalog="description">
      <head>Historical Note</head>
      <p>The Univertsity of Utah was designated the official labor archives of the State of Utah in 1971.  The paper records and audio-visual items created or kept by various Utah labor unions have been deposited here.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="description">
      <p>The Utah labor archive audio-visual collection (1948-1961) consists of 77 audio recordings of speeches and songs relating to labor unions in Utah and the United States at large and 3 16mm films about the labor movement.</p>
    </scopecontent>
    <arrangement encodinganalog="description">
      <p>The majority of the materials are arranged by subject matter and format.</p>
    </arrangement>
    <accessrestrict encodinganalog="rights">
